=================================================
 
The Nature of Britain is a nature documentary series made for British television by the BBC Natural History Unit.
 
 It was first broadcast on BBC1 in October and November 2007. The Nature of Britain was the second BBC natural history series presented by Alan Titchmarsh, following 2004's British Isles - A Natural History.

After the introductory episode, each 50-minute programme showed the wild plants and animals found in a range of different British habitats.
